      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DAM SMOOTH (7) hit the ground running from out wide with a fast early sectional but run over late and missed the frame when a 4 length fourth (30.24) over 520m at this track. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings two times from four attempts. Has ability and can bounce back. CANYA DYNAMITE (2) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when fifth at Q Lakeside over 390m behind Neame (21.98) in a Grade 5. Scored at his previous run. Expected to give a good account. ZIPPING KIMELI (4) won again in another strong performance to make it two on the bounce, scoring by 2.25 lengths (25.60) at Q Lakeside over 457m. In great form and can continue his winning ways. BEST EDITION (6) should bounce back after an unplaced effort here recently.",
